      "comment": "PAW ZENITH (7) had been racing well with a Grade 5 win three back then placed next time before missing the frame latest at Shepparton. Looks suited here and big improvement expected. ROSIE'S CHATTER (5) took advantage of the inside draw with an all-the-way win last start (26.00) at Warragul in a Mix 6/7 over 460m. Comes through a solid form race last start. Can make it two on the bounce. BELFAST SPOT (2) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing fourth (30.41) in a Grade 5 at The Meadows. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings seven times from 12 attempts. Has ability and a bold showing is expected. GUMTREE HILL (1) should be thereabouts after filling a top-three spot most recently.",
